16
17 WHEREAS, Scouting was first established by Englishman Lord Robert
18 Baden-Powell in 1908, and the Boy Scouts of America, the first scouting
19 organization in the United States, was established in the United States on
20 February 8, 1910; and
21
22 WHEREAS, since day one (1), Scouting has espoused the Scout Oath and
23 the twelve (12) points of the Scout Law establishing that a Scout is
24 Trustworthy, Loyal, Helpful, Friendly, Courteous, Kind, Obedient, Cheerful,
25 Thrifty, Brave, Clean, and Reverent; and
26
27 WHEREAS, Scouting includes character development programs such as Cub
28 Scouts, Scouts BSA, Venturing, Sea Scouts, and Exploring that prepare young
29 people through career exploration and skills enrichment programs; and
30
31 WHEREAS, Scouting today exists in two hundred sixteen (216) countries
32 and territories and has fifty million (50,000,000) members worldwide; and
33
34 WHEREAS, Scouting's highest honor, the Eagle Scout award, has instilled
35 in numerous participants a love of service and leadership, including former
36 Presidents of the United States, former Governors of Arkansas, judges,
